So, then,

139
00:07:44.664 --> 00:07:46.966  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-it's possible he could attack at some--
-And now?

140
00:07:47.133 --> 00:07:48.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Huh?

141
00:07:49.001 --> 00:07:50.503  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What is it doing now?

142
00:07:51.971 --> 00:07:54.540  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Uh, now... it's...

143
00:07:56.709 --> 00:07:57.877  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's looking at...

144
00:07:58.778 --> 00:07:59.645  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
At you.

145
00:08:04.817 --> 00:08:05.685  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Hmm.</i>

146
00:08:06.018 --> 00:08:07.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>You insolent little...</i>

147
00:08:08.988 --> 00:08:12.859  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Do you realize how you all have destroyed</i>
<i>my life plans?</i>

148
00:08:14.861 --> 00:08:16.896  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Watch closely, Shimomura.

149
00:08:17.964 --> 00:08:20.500  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The only reason you're on this side
of the glass

150
00:08:20.800 --> 00:08:23.669  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
is because I'm protecting you
behind the scenes.

151
00:08:25.872 --> 00:08:27.206  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Just do your work.

152
00:08:28.741 --> 00:08:29.775  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Or else you will...

153
00:08:31.644 --> 00:08:32.645  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
end up like that.

154
00:08:32.712 --> 00:08:34.280  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Izumi whimpering]

155
00:08:35.515 --> 00:08:37.550  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Futoi]
His reactions are growing sluggish.

156
00:08:37.884 --> 00:08:39.151  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Wakai]
Time to reset him.

157
00:08:39.952 --> 00:08:42.688  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Okay, kill him for now and take a break.

158
00:08:44.790 --> 00:08:45.725  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kondo] Whew.

159
00:08:45.791 --> 00:08:48.528  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Okay, break time.
-[Nomura] We made a lot of progress.

160
00:08:50.096 --> 00:08:51.564  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kei]<i> It's too awful.</i>

161
00:08:52.698 --> 00:08:54.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Why is this...</i>

162
00:08:55.167 --> 00:08:56.636  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>happening to me?</i>

163
00:08:58.004 --> 00:08:59.839  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Kondo]
All right, I'll leave the rest to you.

164
00:09:00.072 --> 00:09:00.940  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Nomura] Fine.

165
00:09:02.642 --> 00:09:03.676  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kei]<i> All I wanted...</i>

166
00:09:05.011 --> 00:09:06.078  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>was to be...</i>

167
00:09:07.547 --> 00:09:09.248  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>an upstanding person.</i>

168
00:09:11.284 --> 00:09:12.151  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>This is...</i>

169
00:09:12.952 --> 00:09:14.987  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>just too horrible.</i>

170
00:09:20.927 --> 00:09:22.261  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's wrong?

171
00:09:22.895 --> 00:09:24.096  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I thought that you said

172
00:09:24.163 --> 00:09:26.732  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
that you didn't wanna become
someone like me?

173
00:09:27.633 --> 00:09:28.301  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasps]

174
00:09:30.336 --> 00:09:31.203  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Tanaka chuckles]

175
00:09:32.071 --> 00:09:32.939  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Tanaka]<i> Really?</i>

176
00:09:34.106 --> 00:09:36.075  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Who are you to look at me like that?</i>

177
00:09:37.577 --> 00:09:39.078  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Kei]
<i>There are horrible humans out there.</i>

178
00:09:39.879 --> 00:09:41.948  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>But like you, Mr. Sato,</i>

179
00:09:42.715 --> 00:09:44.684  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I don't see humans as enemies.</i>

180
00:09:46.319 --> 00:09:50.022  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Tanaka]
Pretending to be the voice of justice.

181
00:09:52.024 --> 00:09:54.060  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do you finally get it now?

182
00:09:55.127 --> 00:09:56.896  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You knew nothing of hell.

183
00:09:56.963 --> 00:09:59.298  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You were just trying to look cool,
weren't you?

184
00:09:59.665 --> 00:10:04.704  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasping]

185
00:10:05.705 --> 00:10:09.108  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Tanaka] <i>You look down on others,</i>
<i>but when you get right to it,</i>

186
00:10:09.175 --> 00:10:11.143  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>you still want them to help you.</i>

187
00:10:11.210 --> 00:10:13.713  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>You're the worst kind of trash.</i>

188
00:10:16.382 --> 00:10:17.717  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>That's right.</i>

189
00:10:19.185 --> 00:10:20.052  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Kill.</i>

190
00:10:21.654 --> 00:10:22.788  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Kill.</i>

191
00:10:22.955 --> 00:10:25.091  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Release your true self!</i>

192
00:10:33.332 --> 00:10:35.167  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Nomura gasps] Hmm?

193
00:10:35.768 --> 00:10:36.669  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Was that wind?

194
00:10:37.336 --> 00:10:38.971  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why did you stop?

195
00:10:39.038 --> 00:10:41.107  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Kai's not coming to help you anymore!

196
00:10:41.173 --> 00:10:43.109  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And Sato might have been captured!

197
00:10:47.380 --> 00:10:48.814  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kei] If I did that...

198
00:10:50.249 --> 00:10:51.684  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Kai might hate me.

199
00:10:52.985 --> 00:10:54.053  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I think...

200
00:10:55.955 --> 00:10:58.090  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Kai's the only one I can't betray.

201
00:10:59.859 --> 00:11:02.294  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Tanaka] Even though
all this is happening to you?

202
00:11:02.361 --> 00:11:05.297  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Killing just one person wouldn't count
as a betrayal!

203
00:11:05.998 --> 00:11:07.066  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kei] No...

204
00:11:07.833 --> 00:11:08.801  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[chuckles]

205
00:11:09.101 --> 00:11:11.437  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If you kill someone,
you could never go back

206
00:11:11.704 --> 00:11:13.672  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
to living a normal life.

207
00:11:14.306 --> 00:11:15.708  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's what you're afraid of.

208
00:11:15.875 --> 00:11:16.742  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kei] No!

209
00:11:17.309 --> 00:11:18.177  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ha!

210
00:11:19.745 --> 00:11:21.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Hit the nail on the head.
-No!

211
00:11:22.715 --> 00:11:23.382  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Kai...

212
00:11:25.251 --> 00:11:26.886  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Kai risked his life.

213
00:11:27.453 --> 00:11:28.954  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He did it for me.

214
00:11:32.124 --> 00:11:33.959  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And he only has one life.

215
00:11:38.864 --> 00:11:39.999  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But I'm not...

216
00:11:41.100 --> 00:11:43.302  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Not even able to risk my life.

217
00:11:44.804 --> 00:11:45.471  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So...

218
00:11:48.007 --> 00:11:50.810  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
So, if I don't risk
everything else I have,

219
00:11:52.478 --> 00:11:54.313  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
it just won't be enough!

220
00:11:56.816 --> 00:11:58.117  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[knife clangs]

221
00:11:59.118 --> 00:12:00.286  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasps]

222
00:12:00.453 --> 00:12:02.121  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[beeping]

223
00:12:02.354 --> 00:12:04.023  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Nomura] Okay, time for round two.

224
00:12:04.190 --> 00:12:05.324  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kei whimpering]

225
00:12:09.361 --> 00:12:12.131  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Tahara] Our orders from above are
to cause as much pain as possible.

226
00:12:12.298 --> 00:12:14.133  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[whirring]

227
00:12:14.900 --> 00:12:17.269  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Okay, let's start with the teeth
this time.

228
00:12:18.070 --> 00:12:20.072  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[whimpering]

229
00:12:20.239 --> 00:12:22.475  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[drill whirring and Kei screaming]

230
00:12:33.819 --> 00:12:35.321  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Nekozawa] Here's what you asked for.

231
00:12:36.188 --> 00:12:39.892  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Sorry to make you come up
with all these supplies, Mr. Nekozawa.

232
00:12:40.392 --> 00:12:43.229  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Not at all.
I'm glad to help a valued client.

233
00:12:44.163 --> 00:12:46.832  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, in that case,
our goods are in here.

234
00:12:47.266 --> 00:12:49.401  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I look forward to working with you again.

235
00:12:49.902 --> 00:12:51.070  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And you as well.

236
00:12:56.809 --> 00:12:58.544  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[door opens, then closes]

237
00:13:00.813 --> 00:13:02.248  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hey, Mr. Nekozawa.

238
00:13:02.548 --> 00:13:04.950  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Don't you think
that you should check inside first?

239
00:13:05.017 --> 00:13:06.152  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why? I trust him.

240
00:13:06.218 --> 00:13:07.453  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You trust him, really?

241
00:13:07.820 --> 00:13:11.457  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Ten livers, ten kidneys
and even some hearts.

242
00:13:11.991 --> 00:13:13.792  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you sure they're really in there?

243
00:13:15.161 --> 00:13:17.263  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yeah. They're definitely in there.

244
00:13:18.230 --> 00:13:19.565  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Where would he get them all?

245
00:13:20.266 --> 00:13:21.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Who knows?

246
00:13:21.901 --> 00:13:25.137  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
However, the man always delivers.

247
00:13:26.872 --> 00:13:28.073  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Even if it kills him.

248
00:13:30.176 --> 00:13:32.344  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[cameraman] Okay, we're rolling.
-[man 1] Here he comes!

249
00:13:32.411 --> 00:13:34.180  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[man 2] Here we go.
-[cameraman] There.

250
00:13:34.580 --> 00:13:35.514  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man 3] Roll cameras.

251
00:13:35.581 --> 00:13:39.151  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Breaking news.
Dr. Ikuya Ogura has just arrived.

252
00:13:39.218 --> 00:13:41.487  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's his second trip to Japan
for an inspection,

253
00:13:41.554 --> 00:13:45.224  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
along with the time when the country's
second Ajin, Tanaka, was caught.

254
00:13:46.525 --> 00:13:49.228  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ever since going to the U.S. in 1999,

255
00:13:49.295 --> 00:13:53.299  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
biophysicist Dr. Ogura has been known
as an authority on Ajin research.

256
00:13:54.033 --> 00:13:57.303  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[chattering]

257
00:14:00.839 --> 00:14:02.241  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Sato] Unfortunate weather.

258
00:14:04.543 --> 00:14:07.012  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They're harder to control in the rain.

259
00:14:08.247 --> 00:14:10.282  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Tanaka, get to work on plan C.

260
00:14:10.883 --> 00:14:13.052  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Abducting some doctor called Ogura, right?

261
00:14:13.552 --> 00:14:17.623  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And I will take plan B,
which is to rescue Kei Nagai.

262
00:14:20.192 --> 00:14:23.329  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
All right then,
how shall we storm the castle?

263
00:14:25.130 --> 00:14:26.465  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The answer is simple.

264
00:14:26.866 --> 00:14:30.002  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We attack the enemy with more firepower
than they're expecting.

265
00:14:30.169 --> 00:14:34.607  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Then using everything we've got,
we roll right over them.

266
00:14:37.009 --> 00:14:40.112  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>Countries over the world are competing</i>
<i>with their research on Ajins,</i>

267
00:14:40.179 --> 00:14:43.148  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>but Japan and the U.S.</i>
<i>have a cooperative research agreement,</i>

268
00:14:43.315 --> 00:14:46.418  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>and Dr. Ogura's visit to Japan</i>
<i>has been reported as a part of that.</i>

269
00:14:46.485 --> 00:14:48.654  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I see that a VIP has arrived.

270
00:14:48.921 --> 00:14:50.623  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hmph. He's just an idiot.

271
00:14:51.657 --> 00:14:53.459  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's quite a thing to say.

272
00:14:53.525 --> 00:14:57.263  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This thing with Japan and the U.S.
is nothing more than a front.

273
00:14:57.563 --> 00:15:00.900  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
In truth, we're being forced
into providing them with information.

274
00:15:01.533 --> 00:15:03.168  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Oh, really?
-In fact,

275
00:15:03.235 --> 00:15:06.639  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
the first Ajin in this country was stolen
by the Americans.

276
00:15:06.906 --> 00:15:08.407  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
So, it's no wonder
the researchers might--

277
00:15:08.474 --> 00:15:10.342  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[explosion, rumbling, then all gasping]

278
00:15:10.409 --> 00:15:12.177  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What was that? An earthquake?

279
00:15:12.244 --> 00:15:13.445  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kouma] No, an explosion.

280
00:15:13.512 --> 00:15:15.981  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[guard] <i>This is the security office!</i>
<i>There's an intruder!</i>

281
00:15:16.282 --> 00:15:18.217  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>The man in the hat has gotten inside!</i>

282
00:15:18.284 --> 00:15:21.387  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Did he come to rescue Nagai?
After leaving him behind?

283
00:15:21.453 --> 00:15:24.156  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-<i>We're gonna counterattack!</i>
-Wait, don't kill him! He's an Ajin!

284
00:15:24.323 --> 00:15:26.992  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[gunshot, then guard grunts]
[all gasp]

285
00:15:28.661 --> 00:15:31.697  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Are you there watching, Tosaki?</i>

286
00:15:32.298 --> 00:15:33.165  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grumbles]

287
00:15:33.565 --> 00:15:36.001  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>The actual reason I'm here--</i>

288
00:15:36.068 --> 00:15:37.603  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>You don't understand yet.</i>

289
00:15:38.270 --> 00:15:39.238  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>But...</i>

290
00:15:39.605 --> 00:15:45.344  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>This evening, the Ajin situation</i>
<i>in Japan will change dramatically.</i>

291
00:15:45.644 --> 00:15:46.512  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
CALL DISCONNECTED

292
00:15:46.578 --> 00:15:47.546  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Tosaki gasps]

293
00:15:47.613 --> 00:15:49.281  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What are you going to do, Tosaki?

294
00:15:49.348 --> 00:15:53.018  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Nagai hasn't shown variant power
since the first experiments.

295
00:15:53.085 --> 00:15:55.721  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Futoi]
If Nagai is taken, our research will be--

296
00:15:56.088 --> 00:15:57.523  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We've reinforced our security.

297
00:15:57.589 --> 00:16:00.392  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If just a single tranquilizer dart
hits its mark,

298
00:16:01.160 --> 00:16:05.297  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
there may be collateral damage,
but we assuredly will win.

299
00:16:06.365 --> 00:16:07.433  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kouma] Hmm.

300
00:16:09.301 --> 00:16:12.037  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I grant you the effectiveness
of the tranquilizers.

301
00:16:12.104 --> 00:16:13.405  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But why don't you just kill him?

302
00:16:13.739 --> 00:16:14.707  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If things go wrong,

303
00:16:14.974 --> 00:16:17.209  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-we could all be in danger!
-Remember the incident

304
00:16:17.276 --> 00:16:18.310  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
with Shinya Nakamura?

305
00:16:19.044 --> 00:16:22.414  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If we carelessly kill an Ajin,
another tragedy could occur.

306
00:16:22.581 --> 00:16:26.251  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Therefore, killing them...
it's a worst-case scenario.

307
00:16:28.620 --> 00:16:29.488  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[man 1]
Move, move!

308
00:16:29.655 --> 00:16:31.323  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[man 2] Hurry!
-[man 3] Cover the side!

309
00:16:31.390 --> 00:16:32.691  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man 4] Fire them one at a time!

310
00:16:33.258 --> 00:16:34.226  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Don't fire all at once!

311
00:16:34.293 --> 00:16:37.062  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If he's hit with too many tranquilizers,
he could die of shock.

312
00:16:37.229 --> 00:16:39.164  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[man 5]
Make sure the safety's off! Stay alert.

313
00:16:40.466 --> 00:16:42.067  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gunshot, then man grunts]

314
00:16:43.135 --> 00:16:44.069  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man 1] He's coming!

315
00:16:44.236 --> 00:16:45.704  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let's do this.

316
00:16:47.039 --> 00:16:48.007  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man yells indistinctly]

317
00:17:08.093 --> 00:17:08.761  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man] Careful.

318
00:17:13.732 --> 00:17:16.635  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[all grunting and screaming]

319
00:17:30.549 --> 00:17:31.417  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunts]

320
00:17:32.084 --> 00:17:33.786  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I didn't even have to use it.

321
00:17:36.188 --> 00:17:37.623  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now then, Nagai...

322
00:17:38.323 --> 00:17:40.059  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've come to see you.

323
00:17:44.463 --> 00:17:45.631  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[all gasp]

324
00:17:46.432 --> 00:17:47.366  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kouma grunts]

325
00:17:47.533 --> 00:17:50.702  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Close all the security doors!
Do you intend to let him get in here?

326
00:17:51.804 --> 00:17:53.505  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Just who is that Ajin?

327
00:17:53.672 --> 00:17:57.209  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I only know one thing:
he stole Tanaka earlier,

328
00:17:57.276 --> 00:17:59.778  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and now, he is attempting
to steal Kei Nagai as well.

329
00:17:59.845 --> 00:18:00.712  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Damn it!

330
00:18:00.779 --> 00:18:02.648  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Kishi]
From what we can see on the screen,

331
00:18:02.714 --> 00:18:05.484  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
he doesn't seem to be using
his variant power.

332
00:18:05.551 --> 00:18:06.752  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Wakai] Why didn't he use it?

333
00:18:07.386 --> 00:18:10.789  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
When he came for Tanaka,
it caused a great deal of casualties.

334
00:18:11.390 --> 00:18:15.094  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Perhaps he actually did use it,
but we just didn't see it.

335
00:18:17.162 --> 00:18:18.664  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Ogura] Of course you wouldn't see it.

336
00:18:21.467 --> 00:18:23.669  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Humans aren't capable of seeing it.

337
00:18:29.274 --> 00:18:30.142  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Tanaka] Huh?

338
00:18:31.343 --> 00:18:32.211  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[scoffs]

339
00:18:32.544 --> 00:18:33.512  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He got away.

340
00:18:38.884 --> 00:18:41.253  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Man, why all the commotion?

341
00:18:42.221 --> 00:18:44.556  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Even though the great Ikuya Ogura is here.

342
00:18:44.623 --> 00:18:46.859  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm sorry, it's an emergency.

343
00:18:47.226 --> 00:18:48.894  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You can't smoke in here.

344
00:18:49.495 --> 00:18:50.796  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kouma] Dr. Ogura,

345
00:18:50.863 --> 00:18:54.333  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
you just said that humans
can't see the variant power, right?

346
00:18:54.700 --> 00:18:56.869  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-What does that mean?
-Well, just that.

347
00:18:57.369 --> 00:19:00.472  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You were talking about IBMs,
isn't that right?

348
00:19:00.539 --> 00:19:01.673  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kishi] IBM?

349
00:19:02.374 --> 00:19:05.144  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Wakai] That's what they call
the variant power in the U.S.

350
00:19:05.377 --> 00:19:08.247  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-It stands for--
-[Ogura] Invisible Black Matter.

351
00:19:08.413 --> 00:19:12.618  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
IBMs can't be seen by humans,
but they're shaped like us.

352
00:19:12.684 --> 00:19:15.454  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They are the coolest guys there are.

353
00:19:15.821 --> 00:19:17.656  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Completely ridiculous.

354
00:19:18.357 --> 00:19:19.758  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So, this variant power...

355
00:19:19.925 --> 00:19:21.660  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-is like a ghost or something?
-Colonel...

356
00:19:23.595 --> 00:19:26.265  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-You're basically an idiot, aren't you?
-What?

357
00:19:27.232 --> 00:19:30.602  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
IBMs aren't psychic powers or ghosts
or anything,

358
00:19:30.836 --> 00:19:31.904  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
they're solid matter.

359
00:19:32.704 --> 00:19:33.605  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Matter?

360
00:19:44.383 --> 00:19:45.717  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, then, Nagai...

361
00:19:47.686 --> 00:19:50.355  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How have you been handling things?

362
00:20:03.502 --> 00:20:05.804  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Tanaka, do you understand?

363
00:20:06.405 --> 00:20:07.739  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm here to rescue you.

364
00:20:08.307 --> 00:20:10.676  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Tanaka whimpering]

365
00:20:14.780 --> 00:20:17.216  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Right. That's good.

366
00:20:29.261 --> 00:20:31.830  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nagai, do you understand?

367
00:20:32.331 --> 00:20:33.565  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm here to rescue you.

368
00:20:35.667 --> 00:20:36.735  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How long...

369
00:20:38.237 --> 00:20:39.438  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
have I been here?

370
00:20:39.938 --> 00:20:41.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, let's see...

371
00:20:42.341 --> 00:20:43.976  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Over ten days, I believe.

372
00:20:45.577 --> 00:20:47.246  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Only ten days?

373
00:20:48.680 --> 00:20:49.881  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It seems like more.

374
00:20:54.853 --> 00:20:59.858  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kei whimpering, then sobbing]

375
00:21:13.972 --> 00:21:15.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mr. Sato...

376
00:21:18.877 --> 00:21:20.979  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm sorry to have caused such trouble.

377
00:21:23.782 --> 00:21:25.417  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Sato] <i>Well, this was...</i>

378
00:21:26.018 --> 00:21:27.019  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>a failure.</i>

379
00:21:33.692 --> 00:21:35.460  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
TO BE CONTINUED

380
00:21:42.668 --> 00:21:46.338  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ If my wish would come true ♪</i>

381
00:21:46.571 --> 00:21:48.473  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ Once again ♪</i>

382
00:21:48.740 --> 00:21:51.977  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ I wanna touch your heart ♪</i>

383
00:21:52.477 --> 00:21:57.316  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ No matter how dark it gets ♪</i>

384
00:21:57.683 --> 00:22:00.052  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ I'll be searching ♪</i>

385
00:22:00.819 --> 00:22:02.788  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ For my one ♪</i>

386
00:22:02.854 --> 00:22:05.590  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ And only light ♪</i>

387
00:22:06.758 --> 00:22:09.961  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ As I look up to the stars ♪</i>

388
00:22:10.529 --> 00:22:12.397  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ Even though you are far ♪</i>

389
00:22:12.764 --> 00:22:18.103  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>♪ You're looking up</i>
<i>At the same starry sky ♪</i>

390
00:22:18.603 --> 00:22:21.039  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ In the sky of my heart ♪</i>

391
00:22:21.740 --> 00:22:24.109  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ It's about to spill over ♪</i>

392
00:22:24.710 --> 00:22:26.778  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ Your smile and ♪</i>

393
00:22:26.845 --> 00:22:29.047  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ Your warmth ♪</i>

394
00:22:29.114 --> 00:22:30.348  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ Hear me ♪</i>

395
00:22:30.615 --> 00:22:33.385  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ Until I went away and ♪</i>

396
00:22:33.819 --> 00:22:35.654  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ Faced the lonely days ♪</i>

397
00:22:35.721 --> 00:22:38.957  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ I thought I could understand ♪</i>

398
00:22:39.024 --> 00:22:42.127  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ What it means to love ♪</i>

399
00:22:42.728 --> 00:22:45.530  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ Feeling everything that ♪</i>

400
00:22:45.597 --> 00:22:47.499  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ Was right in front of me ♪</i>

401
00:22:47.566 --> 00:22:50.769  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ Losing something precious ♪</i>

402
00:22:50.836 --> 00:22:55.006  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ Realizing real love ♪</i>

403
00:22:56.708 --> 00:22:57.876  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ I'll tell you now ♪</i>

404
00:22:58.043 --> 00:23:00.879  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ Just how close you are ♪</i>

